<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="481" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> and Prime Minister
                                        <persName>Churchill</persName> to Marshal <persName type="to">Stalin</persName>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d481fn1">Sent to the War Cabinet Office in
                                    London as <gloss target="#t_Churchill1">Churchill</gloss>’s
                                    telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Welfare1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welfare</hi>
                                    </gloss> 218 and forwarded to the British Ambassador in the
                                    Soviet Union (Clark Kerr). Concerning the delivery of this
                                    message in Moscow, see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1062">p. 1062</ref>, fn. 1.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <gloss target="#t_Quadrant1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quadrant</hi>
                                        </gloss></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-19">19 August 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>President and Prime Minister to Marshal Stalin. Most Secret and
                                Personal.</p>
                            <p>Reference our immediately preceding telegram.<note n="2" xml:id="d481fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                                </note>
                            </p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Operation referred to in paragraph 1 is attack on West Coast
                                    of Italian mainland. Code name in paragraph 3 refers to
                                    Portuguese Atlantic islands.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>Following instructions to General Eisenhower referred to in
                                    paragraph 2. <hi rend="italic">Begins:</hi> (Here insert
                                    paraphrased text of <gloss target="#t_Fan1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fan</hi>
                                    </gloss> 196<note n="3" xml:id="d481fn3">For the text of
                                        telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Fan1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fan</hi>
                                        </gloss> 196 as dispatched from Quebec on August 18, 1943,
                                        see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1060">p.
                                            1060</ref>. For the paraphrased text of this telegram as
                                        included in the message delivered to Stalin, see <hi rend="italic">Stalin’s Correspondence</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 144–146; vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 80–82.</note>) <hi rend="italic">Ends</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>